OL,3,CIncome inequality in Ireland and
OL,4,CNorthern Ireland 'very similar' ` study
OL,6,FThe study measured income inequality
OL,7,Fusing 2019 data and the Gini
OL,8,Fcoefficient method, where 0% is
OL,9,Fperfect equality and 100% is if all
OL,10,Fincome is held by one person.
OL,12,FDifferences in demographics, working
OL,13,Fpatterns, wage levels and the tax-
OL,14,Fbenefit system between Ireland and
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland have an effect on how
OL,16,Fincome is distributed differently.
OL,18,FThe research found that differences in
OL,19,Finequality of market incomes north and
OL,20,Fsouth of the border are driven by two
OL,21,Fcounteracting forces.
