OL,3,CIncome inequality in Ireland and
OL,4,CNorthern Ireland 'very similar' ` study
OL,6,FReport co-author Dora Tuda said: "This
OL,7,Fresearch finds that, if there is any
OL,8,Fconvergence in the future between the
OL,9,Ftax-benefit systems of Ireland and
OL,10,FNorthern Ireland there may be a
OL,11,Flimited impact on income inequality
OL,12,Fdue to opposing forces in the tax and
OL,13,Fbenefit system."
OL,15,FMichele Gubello, another report co-
OL,16,Fauthor, said: "Previous ESRI research
OL,17,Findicates that most of the population
OL,18,Fof Ireland and Northern Ireland
OL,19,Fbelieves that their government should
OL,20,F'reduce income inequality'.
